		<td><b>quick slrom question</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />was working on making an slrom eprom cart and had a quick question
<br />
<br />The info for making one explains:
<br />SLROM (mapper 1):
<br />
<br />
<br />PRG socket:
<br />Bend up pins 1, 2, 24, 30 and 31 (or cut tracks)
<br />Solder pin 2 to hole 24 (A16)
<br />Solder pin 24 to GND (OE)
<br />Solder pin 30 to hole 1 (A17)
<br />
<br />
<br />CHR socket:
<br />Bend up pins 1, 2, 22, 24, 30 and 31 (or cut tracks)
<br />Solder pin 2 to hole 24 (A16)
<br />Solder pin 22 to hole 31 (CE or CHR /A13)
<br />Solder pin 24 to hole 2 (OE or CHR /RD)
<br />
<br />
<br />these are for a 27CXXX series, when I compare the datasheet for one I notice that 27CXXX chip has 5V for pin 1
<br />
<br />Why is pin 1 left floating? shouldn't it be tied down to 5V?
<br />
<br />thanks

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
